Ringo is our Rescue of the Week! He's a French Bulldog available through Badass Bulldog Rescue who is looking for his forever home!

Here's an intro from Ringo himself:
"I am a 2 and ½ year old merle male.  I have Laryngeal Paralysis, a condition where my windpipe fails to open correctly when breathing in.  Surgery can be done (Tie Back) but we have been told by a few vest it usually fails because the tissue is too soft.  There are things to help.  No collars, only harnesses.  3-4 small meals a day, dry food soaked with water.  Keep me lean and in shape. Also keep me out of hot humid weather as much as possible.

Looking for a home that understands my condition to give me the best life possible.  I love my toys, the plush toys that squeak are my favorite, I will suckle on them and fall right to sleep.  I become the Fun Police when my foster siblings are playing and try to break it up.  I have to be in the mood to play with other dogs and would prefer a sibling that is not that playful.  I am great in the car and I am ready to go anytime.  At bedtime, I will want to sleep in your bed right next to you.  If you don’t like snoring, I am not the dog for you.  My breathing, when relaxed becomes louder, so you will need to get used to it or buy earplugs.  I am shy at first but once I get you know you I will give you unconditional love and attention, I just want that in return."

Learn more about Ringo and the other dogs @badass_bulldog_rescue https://www.badassbullyrescue.com/adoptable-dogs

Available foster Margo LOVES to play! She also expects that you’ll keep playing fetch as long as she keeps looking this cute when she brings her toy back to you—and she’s right! 💗 

The perfect home for Margo will be one with lots of people around to play with her and shower her with attention. She would also like to be be the only pet in her home. Margo would thrive in just about any type of home or apartment as long as she has lots of opportunities to exercise and has playtime with toys inside. Margo does not like to be alone and the perfect family for her will include someone who is home most of the time. Margo would be a great dog to bring with you to the office! She is calm and would be quiet while her person is working. She’s also a really smart girl who knows “sit,” “stay,” and “come”.

If you’re smitten with Margo, please read her complete bio and complete an application today! Margo does great in the car and loves to travel, but because she can’t stand being crated, she’s not a good candidate for plane flights. So, if you’re selected to be her forever person be prepared for a road trip as this pretty princess is being fostered in Northern Kentucky and will not be shipped.

https://frenchbulldogrescue.org/available-dogs/margo/ @frenchbulldogrescue

🇺🇸This weekend is the kick-off to summer for many of us and others the first of several outdoor activities. Help your furry family stay safe for Memorial Day with these pet safety tips 🇺🇸

🌭No to the barbecue bones. Having a BBQ? Make sure to not give table scraps, especially bones, to your pets.

⛺️Hiking or camping on the calendar? Don’t forget to pack a lot of water and have a suitable area for shade.
 
🎆Fireworks? This beautiful blast of fun and noise can scare our furry ones. Make sure you have their ID tags up to date and they are microchipped.

☀️Sunny Day? Unless you have sunscreen or insect repellent specifically made for animals, this can be toxic for pets. Watch for signs of drooling, vomiting, diarrhea, excessive thirst, or lethargy as this could be a sign of ingestion.

It’s expected to be a hot one this weekend! As we enter these summer months, we want everyone to be aware of what to look for with heat exhaustion/stroke. 
What temperatures feel okay to us, may feel hotter to our furry friends. 

Limit outside time, and always provide fresh water when playing outside 🩵

With fireworks around the corner, it's important to prep early and find ways to soothe your pets. Save & Share these tips with fellow pet parents and explore additional calming solutions: https://chwy.co/3J9ex9b @chewy

Please welcome beautiful Malia to the available page! This brindle girl arrived in FBRN care from a commercial breeding facility. Now she is ready for a loving forever home where she can be a cherished pet!

Malia’s foster mom had this to say about her, “Malia (also known as Mimi) is a wonderful dog. So sweet and funny and snuggly. I can only imagine that she had a tough start in life but it doesn’t get her down. She settled into life at my house as if she always lived there. Everyone that meets her falls in love!”

If you think you can give Malia the perfect forever home, then all you need to do is fill out an application to adopt. After that, get ready to pick her up in Southern Massachusetts should you be selected as her forever home! ⭐️For detailed information about the dogs in our care, please read the extensive bios on each dog.⭐️

FBRN does not ship dogs as cargo, so adopters are expected to pick up their dogs from their foster family.

FBRN dogs are in foster care in people’s private homes. For the foster families’ safety, we do not disclose specific locations, and we don’t set up meet and greets prior to applications.

https://frenchbulldogrescue.org/available-dogs/malia/ @frenchbulldogrescue

The devastating Wildfires in Maui have claimed the lives of 96 individuals, marking it as the deadliest fire in a century. The fire has ravaged over 2,000 acres of land, with containment at 85% as of the latest update. The catastrophe has also taken a toll on numerous pets and wildlife, leading to the loss of thousands of animals and forcing those who lost their homes to relinquish their pets to shelters. 

To aid the relief efforts, we’ve created our new "Maui Strong" design, with 100% of net profits from its sales pledged to the @mauihumanesociety , an organization at the forefront of rescue efforts. We hope to emulate the successful fundraising efforts we’ve had for past crises such as the Australian and West Coast fires. 

As always, if you already have enough ATA shirts and still want to support. Please go directly to Maui Humane Society and donate directly. Thank you all of being a part of our amazing community.  You all have made it possible for us to help make a difference! #armtheanimals @mauihumanesociety #mauistrong I also have a link to donate to them in my bio 😔🙏🏻❤️

Always good to know or remind yourself that it can take a while for our rescued friends to settle in, learn a routine, and comfortably relax in their new environment. The 3-3-3 rule sets basic expectations for the first 3 months in their forever home. 🏡

Adopt me!! Hey there, my name is Cinnamon!  At 3-years-old, I’m a Terrier mix girl who had a rough start to life. Due to my timid and shy ways, I prefer to be the only pup in the home.  My human friends at Paws Place do not believe I was socialized much.  Thankfully, they have been so patient with me and let me settle in at my own pace.  I know there is love in the world, and that my person is out there somewhere.  A good routine, patience and support is all I need to find comfort in a new home.  Once I find my zen, I’m a laid-back, 43-pound snuggle bug!  Could you give your heart to me?  Paws Place Dog Rescue is open Tuesday through Saturday from 10am to 2pm and no appointment is necessary.  You can also call 910-845-7297 or email info@pawsplace.org for adoption information. 🐾 Visit www.pawprintsmagazine.com and tap on the cover to meet other adoptable pets in the latest issue. @pawsplacerescue

🐾Pancreatitis can affect our furry friends, both canine and feline! 🐱🐶

As a pet owner, it's important to know the signs of pancreatitis and understand the causes in order to help prevent this concerning condition. 

🔎Pancreatitis in pets is an inflammation of the pancreas that disrupts its normal function. An inflamed pancreas struggles to produce enzymes needed for digestion, leading to poor absorption of nutrients, vomiting, diarrhea, and weight loss. Left untreated, pets are at risk for dangerous health conditions such as dehydration and organ failure. 

Various causes for pancreatitis can be identified but a common factor (🦃especially during holiday seasons🎄) is dietary indiscretion. Pets who consume large amounts of fatty foods in a short period of time can overwhelm their pancreas, this can happen when a pet gets into the trash or eats too many table scraps.🍗🦴🍔🥓🍟🍕🍦

🚨Early detection and treatment is key!🚨 If you notice any signs or suspect your pet has pancreatitis- contact us immediately. If we're unavailable, contact your nearest emergency veterinary facility for advice.
